crease aggro-generating capabilities.  Have any of you warriors ever seen a monk or rogue pull aggro from sheer dps?  I anticipate the same scenario would happen if warriors were &quot;buffed up&quot; in the dps department.<br>
I do good enough damage, in my opinion.  Not too worried about dps.  Strap on a war marshall's staff and a warrior does adequate enough damage--just an example.   <br>
What really irks me, badly, is that soe tries to fix warrior-aggro with gear.  High-end gear, mind you, that drops in Ssra and other such places that not everyone can raid in order to get things such as a hategiver, etc.  Now, compound that, with the fact that pure hate procing weapons are some of the most expensive things in the game to try to purchase.  If I recall correctly, Shanana has a blade of carnage for sale at the one-time low price of 300,000 platinum.  So, in essence, that leaves young warriors who aren't in rich, strong guilds, in the dirt.  <br>
